related_questions.question: How much money does an FBI agent make a year?
related_questions.snippet: Beginning Pay FBI agents are on the federal government's law enforcement pay schedule. They begin at the GS-10, step 1 level. This pay grade pays $45,771 per year in 2011. With locality pay and availability pay, first-year agents can earn between $64,365 to $73,634 per year depending upon where they are stationed.
